<HL>
   Spain Names Labor Minister
</HL>
<DATE>
04/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   MADRID -- Spanish Prime Minister Felipe Gonzalez named
Luis Martinez Noval, a 41-year-old Socialist deputy and
economist, as his new Minister of Labor.
   Mr. Martinez Noval succeeds Manuel Chaves, who was
designated the Socialist party's candidate to head the
regional government of Andalucia in elections set for June
23.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The cabinet change is the only one Mr. Gonzalez is
expected to make following his party's victory in last
October's general elections.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
