<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian retail sales in February fell 1.1% from
January, Statistics Canada, a federal agency, said, and the
decline was attributed partly to a decrease in sales of autos
and other vehicles.
   Retail sales rose 2.2% in January and 0.1% in December.
