<HL>
   Business Brief -- Lincoln NC Realty Fund Inc.:
   Silverstone Partners' Offer
   Of $19 Million Is Rejected
</HL>
<DATE>
04/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A16
</SO>
<CO>
   LRF
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Lincoln NC Realty Fund Inc., Palo Alto, Calif., said it
rejected an offer from Silverstone Partners, a closely held
Los Angeles partnership, because it viewed the proposal as
unfair.
   In a letter, Silverstone Partners offered to buy all of
Lincoln's common stock and warrants outstanding at $9.21875 a
share and 3.1 cents a warrant in a transaction valued at
about $19 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In composite trading Friday on the American Stock
Exchange, Lincoln fell 12.5 cents to $8.375.
   Lincoln previously rebuffed Silverstone. In March, the
investment trust terminated a letter of agreement to be
acquired by Silverstone because Lincoln's banker couldn't
confirm the financial fairness of the deal.
   Silverstone, which couldn't be reached to comment, holds
8.6% of Lincoln.
</TEXT>
